description.narrative:
•	3,000 street children and adolescents identified and/or released from detention;
•	5,000 other children at risk of violence, abuse and exploitation in the provinces of Bujumbura Mairie, Rumonge and Ngozi; 
•	6,000 children benefit from catch up education
•	50,000 children benefit from Psychosocial services
•	Up to 170,000 children and adolescents, including IDPS and returnees at higher protection risks monitored
